value.value: The breakdown product of creatine, a constituent of muscle tissue, that is excreted by the kidney and whose serum level is used to evaluate kidney function.
An immunodeficiency state characterized by very low serum IgG and IgA but either a normal or, more frequently, a markedly elevated concentration of polyclonal IgM.
An urothelial carcinoma that arises from the urothelial lining of the prostatic urethra.
An urothelial carcinoma that arises from the urothelial lining of the prostatic ducts.
An invasive prostate carcinoma composed of prostatic basal cells.
An invasive prostate adenocarcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant cells that exhibit neuroendocrine differentiation.
A rare neoplasm arising from specialized prostatic stroma.  This category includes prostatic stromal proliferations of uncertain malignant potential and prostatic stromal sarcomas.

label.value: Prostate Stromal Tumor of Uncertain Malignant Potential

value.value: A neoplastic lesion that arises from the prostate gland stroma.  Morphologic characteristics include hypercellular stroma with scattered atypical cells, prominent overgrowth of the prostatic stroma, or changes resembling benign phyllodes tumor.  The majority of cases do not have an aggressive clinical course.  A minority of cases however, may progress to stromal sarcoma.
An extremely rare adenocarcinoma that arises from the seminal vesicle.
A rare benign cystadenoma that arises from the seminal vesicle.
A benign or malignant neoplasm that affects the seminal vesicle.  Representative examples include cystadenoma and adenocarcinoma.
Thrombocytopenia that results from immune destruction of platelets.

A testicular mixed germ cell-sex cord-stromal tumor.  It is usually associated with mixed gonadal dysgenesis and ambiguous genitalia.  It is characterized by the presence of nests of large neoplastic germ cells and immature cells that resemble Sertoli cells.

label.value: Testicular Mixed Germ Cell-Sex Cord-Stromal Tumor, Unclassified

value.value: A testicular mixed germ cell-sex cord-stromal tumor in which the neoplastic germ cells and the neoplastic sex cord-stromal cells do not form nests and are instead arranged in a diffuse pattern.

A germ cell tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of one histologic component.  This category includes seminoma, teratoma, embryonal carcinoma, yolk sac tumor, and choriocarcinoma.
A chromosome band present on 7p
This gene plays a role in regulation of transcription and the inhibition of apoptosis. It is also involved in the control of morphogenesis during embryonic development.
Twist-related protein 1 (202 aa, ~21 kDa) is encoded by the human TWIST1 gene. This protein plays a role in the negative regulation of both transcription and myogenesis.
A testicular seminoma characterized by the presence of syncytiotrophoblastic giant cells.
The most aggressive form of Kaposi sarcoma. It presents in patients who are infected with the human immunodeficiency virus. It can affect the skin and internal organs.

label.value: Testicular Seminoma with High Mitotic Index

value.value: A seminoma of the testis characterized by increased cellular pleomorphism, high mitotic activity, and a non-prominent stromal lymphocytic infiltrate.

A testicular germ cell tumor derived from postpubertal-type germ cells. It is characterized by the presence of three cell types: round cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm, small cells with dark nucleus and a small amount of cytoplasm, and mono-or multinucleated giant cells. The neoplastic cells are not cohesive. There is an edematous stroma present; lymphocytic infiltrates are rarely seen. Most patients are older males.

A malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of a spermatocytic tumor component that is contiguous with an undifferentiated or differentiated sarcomatous component.  It usually presents as a slowly growing mass that enlarges very rapidly soon after the initial diagnosis.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Microcystic Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of a meshwork of small vacuolated cells resulting in a honeycomb appearance.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Macrocystic Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of collections of thin-walled spaces.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Solid Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of aggregates of polygonal malignant cells with clear cytoplasm and prominent nucleoli.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Glandular-Alveolar Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of gland-like spaces, irregular alveoli, and tubular structures.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Endodermal Sinus/Perivascular Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of connective tissue stalks that contain a blood vessel and are lined by cells with clear cytoplasm and prominent nucleoli.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Papillary Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of numerous papillary structures that are lined by cells with prominent nucleoli.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Myxomatous Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of myxomatous tissue that contains collections of malignant cells with prominent nucleoli.

label.value: Stage II Colon Cancer AJCC v6

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA (T3, N0, M0); IIB (T4, N0, M0).  T3: Tumor invades through the muscularis propria or into non-peritonealized pericolic or perirectal tissues.  T4: Tumor directly invades other organs or structures, and/or perforates visceral peritoneum.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th ed.)

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Polyvesicular Vitelline Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of collections of vesicles that are surrounded by connective tissue.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Hepatoid Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of hepatoid cells collections.

label.value: Testicular Yolk Sac Tumor, Enteric Pattern

value.value: A yolk sac tumor that arises from the testis and is characterized by the presence of immature glands.
A tumor that arises from the testis and is composed of neoplastic trophoblastic cells.  The vast majority of cases are choriocarcinomas.

A choriocarcinoma that arises from the testis and is characterized by the predominance of cytotrophoblastic and intermediate trophoblastic cells.  Syncytiotrophoblastic cells are absent or not prominent.
A teratoma that arises from the testis.  It is composed exclusively of one of the following tissue types: endoderm, ectoderm, or mesoderm.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction as well as protein binding and trafficking.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction and receptor signaling.

label.value: Stage IV Colon Cancer AJCC v6

value.value: Stage IV includes: (Any T, Any N, M1).  M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th ed.)

Exercise Physiology is the identification of physiological mechanisms underlying physical activity, the comprehensive delivery of treatment services concerned with the analysis, improvement, and maintenance of health and fitness, rehabilitation of heart disease and other chronic diseases and/or disabilities, and the professional guidance and counsel of athletes and others interested in athletics, sports training, and human adaptability to acute and chronic exercise. (American Society of Exercise Physiologists)
A chromosome band present on 4q
A Leydig cell tumor characterized by a large size, cellular atypia, high mitotic activity, vascular invasion and necrotic changes.  The prognosis is usually poor.

label.value: Testicular Sertoli Cell Tumor, Lipid Rich Variant

value.value: A testicular Sertoli cell tumor in which the neoplastic cells have clear and vacuolated cytoplasm due to accumulation of intracytoplasmic lipids.

label.value: Testicular Large Cell Calcifying Sertoli Cell Tumor

value.value: A testicular Sertoli cell tumor characterized by the presence of large polygonal cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm in a myxoid and hyalinized stroma. Calcifications may be present in the stroma. Malignant behavior is uncommon.
A rare testicular Sertoli cell tumor characterized by the presence of neoplastic tubules that are surrounded by a dense fibrotic stroma.
